      "text": "There are a range of different arguments for open government data.[http://dx.doi.org/10.2139/ssrn.2605828 Towards a Genealogy of Open Data][http://www.stlr.org/volumes/volume-ix-2007-2008/brito/ Hack, Mash, & Peer: Crowdsourcing Government Transparency] For example, some advocates contend that making government information available to the public as machine readable open data can facilitate government transparency, accountability and public participation. Some make the case that opening up official information can support technological innovation and economic growth by enabling third parties to develop new kinds of digital applications and services - [https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Open_data#Open_data_in_government wikipedia]"
